author: BARINDERJIT SALUJA
description: CBI has filed a chargesheet against four Punjab Police personnel, naming Inspector Ronnie Singh as the prime accused in the assault on Colonel Pushpinder Bath. Charges of attempted murder were dropped, replaced with 'causing grievous hurt' and 'wrongful restraint' following a parking dispute.

author: RAMENDRA SINGH
description: India's first wildlife-safe road corridor debuts on Bhopal-Jabalpur highway. A 12km stretch through a tiger reserve features speed-calming red markings, fencing, and 25 underpasses. This integrated approach aims to drastically reduce animal road deaths by guiding wildlife and slowing vehicles in critical tiger habitats.

author: SUKUMAR MAHATO
description: A 20-year-old Bengali mason, working in Odisha for the first time, was tragically beaten to death by a mob. While his family claims he was falsely accused of being Bangladeshi, police state the violence erupted from a monetary dispute. Two other migrant workers were critically injured in the attack.

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A casual chat about weight loss between a US envoy and Belarus's leader, Alexander Lukashenko, unexpectedly paved the way for releasing over 120 political prisoners.  The personal exchange, involving a prescription drug, helped break the ice for crucial negotiations on sanctions relief and prisoner swaps, ultimately reuniting families and easing US restrictions on key Belarusian exports.
title: More than medicine: How a weight-loss drug helped US envoy free prisoners in Belarus

author: TNN
description: Indian Army eases social media restrictions for its soldiers, allowing limited access to platforms like Instagram for viewing and monitoring.  Skype, WhatsApp, Telegram, and Signal can be used for exchanging unclassified information with known contacts. YouTube, X, Quora, and LinkedIn also have specific, restricted uses, focusing on passive information gathering and professional networking, a significant shift from previous blanket bans.

author: SHARIQ MAJEED
description: In a heartwarming display of unity, a 75-year-old Sikh woman in Punjab's Jakhwali village donated land for a new mosque. Sikh and Hindu families are also contributing financially to the construction. This gesture highlights the village's long-standing tradition of interfaith harmony, where all communities support each other's religious needs.

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Former Chelsea star Frank Lampard, a decorated player and manager, has achieved significant success in football. description: Tragedy struck near Mysuru Palace late Thursday when a helium cylinder for balloons exploded, claiming one life and injuring four, including three tourists. Despite initial signage and road access challenges, the airport marks a major expansion for the region's connectivity.

Advocacy groups warn of increased profiling and wider economic disruption.

Citing misuse for bypassing cyber restrictions and accessing prohibited content, the order aims to prevent unlawful activities and protect sensitive data. The district magistrate's directive mandates strict enforcement, with violations facing legal consequences.

description: Delhi’s Directorate of Education has fixed January 10 as the deadline for private schools to form fee regulation committees for the 2025–26 academic year. Under the new process, schools must place their proposed charges before these committees—where parents and teachers are represented—by January 25. Decisions must follow within 30 days, shifting fee discussions from sudden announcements to a defined, time-bound process that parents can track.

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Navi Mumbai International Airport became operational on Thursday with the landing of an IndiGo flight from Bengaluru, nearly three decades after it was conceived to ease congestion at Mumbai’s primary airport. description: Indian Railways has announced a fare "rationalisation" effective December 26, aiming for affordability and operational sustainability. Mail/Express and AC/Non-AC ordinary services will see modest increases, with specific graded hikes for non-suburban ordinary journeys.

description: Delhi's air quality saw a welcome improvement for the second day, moving from 'severe' to 'poor' levels. While some areas experienced 'moderate' air, others remained in 'poor' or 'very poor' categories. Vehicular emissions and neighbouring NCR districts were identified as major pollution sources. Forecasts suggest a potential return to 'very poor' conditions soon.

description: Delhi schools have ended hybrid learning and resumed normal physical classes for students of Classes 6 to 9 and 11 after GRAP 4 measures were lifted. The Directorate of Education issued directions to government and private schools to implement the change immediately. The decision followed an improvement in air quality, with authorities continuing GRAP stages 1 to 3 while monitoring conditions closely across the capital.

description: At least seven Hindu families in Bangladesh have had their homes burnt down in targeted attacks over the past five days amidst national turmoil. author: TOI Education
description: Teachers are increasingly hearing anxiety and emotional fatigue instead of academic doubts in classrooms. The Student Sync Index 2026 reveals that student stress is constant, with mental health concerns now outweighing academic pressure. While teachers recognise this shift and respond with empathy, the roots of stress are often externalised, leaving school systems largely unchanged.

description: Jason Kelce opens up about how rising fame after retirement is affecting everyday life with wife Kylie Kelce and their four children. Class 10 board exams will become biannual from 2026, allowing score improvement. APAAR ID linkage is now mandatory for Classes 9–12. Exam fees have increased, while syllabi align with NCF 2023. New career guidance, mental health counselling models, and an AI-powered digital experience centre aim to reduce stress and modernise learning for students, parents, and schools nationwide and abroad too.

description: The Army has unveiled new social media guidelines for its personnel. LinkedIn is permitted for professional networking and job seeking purposes only.

description: America’s H-1B visa process has picked up a new gatekeeper: your social media. description: Scientists have found a unique geological and biological complex deep in the Greenland Sea. This discovery offers new insights into Arctic oceanography and methane stability.
